results.overview:
Welcome to P.S. 152, School of Science & Technology! We are excited to share our approach to teaching, learning, and the special opportunities that make our school a vibrant community for students to grow. At PS 152 School of Science & Technology, our mission is to empower all of our students to respect each other and succeed in all academic and social-emotional areas. Through equitable and rigorous instruction and a diverse and inclusive environment, all students at PS 152 will work to their full potential to become leaders and lifelong learners. 

Our beloved mascot, Oliver the Owl, represents the wisdom, kindness, and adventurous spirit we strive to instill in all of our students. Oliver reminds us every day that “We are WISE,” both in the classroom and beyond. We work hard and take risks. We are inclusive and inspiring. We show respect and kindness. We are enthusiastic learners.

In addition to a rich academic program, we offer a wide variety of enrichment activities to help students explore their interests and talents. These include:

- Basketball and Sports Clubs: Encouraging teamwork, physical fitness, and sportsmanship.
- Dance Team: Offering students the chance to express themselves through movement and performance.
- Art Clubs: Where creativity and imagination take center stage as students explore different mediums.
- Chorus and Drumming: Promoting musical expression and collaboration through voice and percussion.
- STEM and Coding Clubs: Engaging young minds in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics with hands-on projects and coding challenges.
- Hydroponics Club: An innovative program where students learn about sustainable farming practices and plant growth without soil.

We are also proud to have a recently renovated outdoor playground, providing a fun, safe space for students to play, stay active, and build friendships during recess and outdoor activities.

At our school, we believe in developing the whole child, offering opportunities for growth academically, socially, and creatively. We can't wait for your family to become a part of our community! No additional priority is given to zoned students for the Gifted & Talented program at this school.
